value.0: From the neck down, this figure very much looks like a human garbed in fine, tailored clothes - though its dull, rubbery black skin belies the fact that this creature has very inhuman origins. Its head, however, is the biggest giveaway. It is completely hairless, and devoid of anything resembling eyes, with a too-large mouth drawn back in an impossibly-wide fiendish grin, revealing a full set of jagged, black teeth.

The Zau'tar House Insignia is an ornate shadesteel brooch decorated with an overlying silver filligree; inset in a line along the length of the brooch are two black sapphires with a larger, deep burgundy-colored garnet centered between them. A series of miniature black pearls surround each of the three gemstones, with slightly larger pearls situated along the border of the brooch like compass points.

The three gemstones are enchanted in such a way that the bearer may call upon the spells held within them. The garnet may be used to summon a displacer beast up to five times per day, while the sapphires can be used to cast Ultravision and Displacement three times per day each.
